{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":760,"text":"This is Pleurobot."},{"time":3400,"text":"Pleurobot is a robot that we designed\nto closely mimic a salamander species"},{"time":7040,"text":"called Pleurodeles waltl."},{"time":9240,"text":"Pleurobot can walk, as you can see here,"},{"time":11520,"text":"and as you'll see later, it can also swim."}]},{"cues":[{"time":14280,"text":"So you might ask,\nwhy did we design this robot?"},{"time":16960,"text":"And in fact, this robot has been designed\nas a scientific tool for neuroscience."},{"time":21400,"text":"Indeed, we designed it\ntogether with neurobiologists"},{"time":23920,"text":"to understand how animals move,"},{"time":25840,"text":"and especially how the spinal cord\ncontrols locomotion."},{"time":29560,"text":"But the more I work in biorobotics,"},{"time":31280,"text":"the more I'm really impressed\nby animal locomotion."},{"time":33920,"text":"If you think of a dolphin swimming\nor a cat running or jumping around,"},{"time":38240,"text":"or even us as humans,"},{"time":39840,"text":"when you go jogging or play tennis,"},{"time":41680,"text":"we do amazing things."},{"time":43880,"text":"And in fact, our nervous system solves\na very, very complex control problem."},{"time":48040,"text":"It has to coordinate\nmore or less 200 muscles perfectly,"},{"time":51160,"text":"because if the coordination is bad,\nwe fall over or we do bad locomotion."},{"time":55560,"text":"And my goal is to understand\nhow this works."}]},{"cues":[{"time":59160,"text":"There are four main components\nbehind animal locomotion."},{"time":62800,"text":"The first component is just the body,"},{"time":64760,"text":"and in fact we should never underestimate"},{"time":66760,"text":"to what extent the biomechanics\nalready simplify locomotion in animals."},{"time":70920,"text":"Then you have the spinal cord,"},{"time":72400,"text":"and in the spinal cord you find reflexes,"},{"time":74400,"text":"multiple reflexes that create\na sensorimotor coordination loop"},{"time":77880,"text":"between neural activity in the spinal cord\nand mechanical activity."},{"time":82000,"text":"A third component\nare central pattern generators."},{"time":85000,"text":"These are very interesting circuits\nin the spinal cord of vertebrate animals"},{"time":88920,"text":"that can generate, by themselves,"},{"time":90560,"text":"very coordinated\nrhythmic patterns of activity"},{"time":93320,"text":"while receiving\nonly very simple input signals."},{"time":95720,"text":"And these input signals"},{"time":96960,"text":"coming from descending modulation\nfrom higher parts of the brain,"},{"time":100040,"text":"like the motor cortex,\nthe cerebellum, the basal ganglia,"},{"time":102760,"text":"will all modulate activity\nof the spinal cord"},{"time":104920,"text":"while we do locomotion."},{"time":106400,"text":"But what's interesting is to what extent\njust a low-level component,"},{"time":109640,"text":"the spinal cord, together with the body,"},{"time":111600,"text":"already solve a big part\nof the locomotion problem."},{"time":114080,"text":"You probably know it by the fact\nthat you can cut the head off a chicken,"},{"time":117532,"text":"it can still run for a while,"},{"time":118937,"text":"showing that just the lower part,\nspinal cord and body,"},{"time":121500,"text":"already solve a big part of locomotion."}]},{"cues":[{"time":123397,"text":"Now, understanding how this works\nis very complex,"},{"time":125880,"text":"because first of all,"},{"time":127200,"text":"recording activity in the spinal cord\nis very difficult."},{"time":129844,"text":"It's much easier to implant electrodes\nin the motor cortex"},{"time":132640,"text":"than in the spinal cord,\nbecause it's protected by the vertebrae."},{"time":135720,"text":"Especially in humans, very hard to do."},{"time":137560,"text":"A second difficulty is that locomotion\nis really due to a very complex"},{"time":141360,"text":"and very dynamic interaction\nbetween these four components."},{"time":144440,"text":"So it's very hard to find out\nwhat's the role of each over time."},{"time":148880,"text":"This is where biorobots like Pleurobot\nand mathematical models"},{"time":152640,"text":"can really help."}]},{"cues":[{"time":155480,"text":"So what's biorobotics?"},{"time":156760,"text":"Biorobotics is a very active field\nof research in robotics"},{"time":159520,"text":"where people want to\ntake inspiration from animals"},{"time":162000,"text":"to make robots to go outdoors,"},{"time":164480,"text":"like service robots\nor search and rescue robots"},{"time":167160,"text":"or field robots."},{"time":168880,"text":"And the big goal here\nis to take inspiration from animals"},{"time":171600,"text":"to make robots that can handle\ncomplex terrain --"},{"time":173960,"text":"stairs, mountains, forests,"},{"time":175600,"text":"places where robots\nstill have difficulties"},{"time":177640,"text":"and where animals\ncan do a much better job."},{"time":179720,"text":"The robot can be a wonderful\nscientific tool as well."},{"time":182240,"text":"There are some very nice projects\nwhere robots are used,"},{"time":184884,"text":"like a scientific tool for neuroscience,\nfor biomechanics or for hydrodynamics."},{"time":188880,"text":"And this is exactly\nthe purpose of Pleurobot."},{"time":191600,"text":"So what we do in my lab\nis to collaborate with neurobiologists"},{"time":194560,"text":"like Jean-Marie Cabelguen,\na neurobiologist in Bordeaux in France,"},{"time":197800,"text":"and we want to make spinal cord models\nand validate them on robots."},{"time":202480,"text":"And here we want to start simple."}]},{"cues":[{"time":204120,"text":"So it's good to start with simple animals"},{"time":206120,"text":"like lampreys, which are\nvery primitive fish,"},{"time":208400,"text":"and then gradually\ngo toward more complex locomotion,"},{"time":210920,"text":"like in salamanders,"},{"time":212200,"text":"but also in cats and in humans,"},{"time":213720,"text":"in mammals."},{"time":215880,"text":"And here, a robot becomes\nan interesting tool"},{"time":218280,"text":"to validate our models."},{"time":220240,"text":"And in fact, for me, Pleurobot\nis a kind of dream becoming true."},{"time":223280,"text":"Like, more or less 20 years ago\nI was already working on a computer"},{"time":226560,"text":"making simulations of lamprey\nand salamander locomotion"},{"time":229240,"text":"during my PhD."},{"time":230800,"text":"But I always knew that my simulations\nwere just approximations."},{"time":234200,"text":"Like, simulating the physics in water\nor with mud or with complex ground,"},{"time":238200,"text":"it's very hard to simulate that\nproperly on a computer."},{"time":240880,"text":"Why not have a real robot\nand real physics?"},{"time":243600,"text":"So among all these animals,\none of my favorites is the salamander."},{"time":246760,"text":"You might ask why,\nand it's because as an amphibian,"},{"time":250240,"text":"it's a really key animal\nfrom an evolutionary point of view."},{"time":253120,"text":"It makes a wonderful link\nbetween swimming,"},{"time":255200,"text":"as you find it in eels or fish,"},{"time":257120,"text":"and quadruped locomotion,\nas you see in mammals, in cats and humans."},{"time":262160,"text":"And in fact, the modern salamander"},{"time":263840,"text":"is very close to the first\nterrestrial vertebrate,"},{"time":266240,"text":"so it's almost a living fossil,"},{"time":267800,"text":"which gives us access to our ancestor,"},{"time":269760,"text":"the ancestor to all terrestrial tetrapods."}]},{"cues":[{"time":273240,"text":"So the salamander swims"},{"time":274640,"text":"by doing what's called\nan anguilliform swimming gait,"},{"time":277160,"text":"so they propagate a nice traveling wave\nof muscle activity from head to tail."},{"time":281440,"text":"And if you place\nthe salamander on the ground,"},{"time":283640,"text":"it switches to what's called\na walking trot gait."},{"time":286000,"text":"In this case, you have nice\nperiodic activation of the limbs"},{"time":288887,"text":"which are very nicely coordinated"},{"time":290520,"text":"with this standing wave\nundulation of the body,"},{"time":293200,"text":"and that's exactly the gait\nthat you are seeing here on Pleurobot."},{"time":296880,"text":"Now, one thing which is very surprising\nand fascinating in fact"},{"time":299880,"text":"is the fact that all this can be generated\njust by the spinal cord and the body."},{"time":304040,"text":"So if you take\na decerebrated salamander --"},{"time":306064,"text":"it's not so nice\nbut you remove the head --"},{"time":308104,"text":"and if you electrically\nstimulate the spinal cord,"},{"time":310800,"text":"at low level of stimulation\nthis will induce a walking-like gait."},{"time":314080,"text":"If you stimulate a bit more,\nthe gait accelerates."},{"time":316560,"text":"And at some point, there's a threshold,"},{"time":318480,"text":"and automatically,\nthe animal switches to swimming."},{"time":321040,"text":"This is amazing."},{"time":322440,"text":"Just changing the global drive,"},{"time":323960,"text":"as if you are pressing the gas pedal"},{"time":325720,"text":"of descending modulation\nto your spinal cord,"},{"time":327880,"text":"makes a complete switch\nbetween two very different gaits."},{"time":332440,"text":"And in fact, the same\nhas been observed in cats."},{"time":335040,"text":"If you stimulate the spinal cord of a cat,"},{"time":337080,"text":"you can switch between\nwalk, trot and gallop."},{"time":339320,"text":"Or in birds, you can make a bird\nswitch between walking,"},{"time":342080,"text":"at a low level of stimulation,"},{"time":343560,"text":"and flapping its wings\nat high-level stimulation."},{"time":346400,"text":"And this really shows that the spinal cord"},{"time":348440,"text":"is a very sophisticated\nlocomotion controller."}]},{"cues":[{"time":350880,"text":"So we studied salamander locomotion\nin more detail,"},{"time":353360,"text":"and we had in fact access\nto a very nice X-ray video machine"},{"time":356480,"text":"from Professor Martin Fischer\nin Jena University in Germany."},{"time":360080,"text":"And thanks to that,\nyou really have an amazing machine"},{"time":362680,"text":"to record all the bone motion\nin great detail."},{"time":365160,"text":"That's what we did."},{"time":366440,"text":"So we basically figured out\nwhich bones are important for us"},{"time":369640,"text":"and collected their motion in 3D."},{"time":372680,"text":"And what we did is collect\na whole database of motions,"},{"time":375400,"text":"both on ground and in water,"},{"time":377080,"text":"to really collect a whole database\nof motor behaviors"},{"time":379589,"text":"that a real animal can do."},{"time":380858,"text":"And then our job as roboticists\nwas to replicate that in our robot."},{"time":384033,"text":"So we did a whole optimization process\nto find out the right structure,"},{"time":387440,"text":"where to place the motors,\nhow to connect them together,"},{"time":390120,"text":"to be able to replay\nthese motions as well as possible."},{"time":393680,"text":"And this is how Pleurobot came to life."}]},{"cues":[{"time":397200,"text":"So let's look at how close\nit is to the real animal."},{"time":400960,"text":"So what you see here\nis almost a direct comparison"},{"time":403480,"text":"between the walking\nof the real animal and the Pleurobot."},{"time":406200,"text":"You can see that we have\nalmost a one-to-one exact replay"},{"time":408960,"text":"of the walking gait."},{"time":410240,"text":"If you go backwards and slowly,\nyou see it even better."},{"time":415520,"text":"But even better, we can do swimming."},{"time":417920,"text":"So for that we have a dry suit\nthat we put all over the robot --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":420960,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":422080,"text":"and then we can go in water\nand start replaying the swimming gaits."},{"time":425280,"text":"And here, we were very happy,\nbecause this is difficult to do."},{"time":428640,"text":"The physics of interaction are complex."},{"time":430880,"text":"Our robot is much bigger\nthan a small animal,"},{"time":433320,"text":"so we had to do what's called\ndynamic scaling of the frequencies"},{"time":436400,"text":"to make sure we had\nthe same interaction physics."},{"time":438760,"text":"But you see at the end,\nwe have a very close match,"},{"time":441200,"text":"and we were very, very happy with this."},{"time":443480,"text":"So let's go to the spinal cord."},{"time":445720,"text":"So here what we did\nwith Jean-Marie Cabelguen"},{"time":448040,"text":"is model the spinal cord circuits."},{"time":451040,"text":"And what's interesting\nis that the salamander"},{"time":453200,"text":"has kept a very primitive circuit,"},{"time":454844,"text":"which is very similar\nto the one we find in the lamprey,"},{"time":457520,"text":"this primitive eel-like fish,"},{"time":459520,"text":"and it looks like during evolution,"},{"time":461280,"text":"new neural oscillators\nhave been added to control the limbs,"},{"time":464240,"text":"to do the leg locomotion."},{"time":465680,"text":"And we know where\nthese neural oscillators are"},{"time":467880,"text":"but what we did was to make\na mathematical model"},{"time":470160,"text":"to see how they should be coupled"},{"time":471800,"text":"to allow this transition\nbetween the two very different gaits."},{"time":474760,"text":"And we tested that on board of a robot."}]},{"cues":[{"time":477680,"text":"And this is how it looks."},{"time":486920,"text":"So what you see here\nis a previous version of Pleurobot"},{"time":489960,"text":"that's completely controlled\nby our spinal cord model"},{"time":493080,"text":"programmed on board of the robot."},{"time":495280,"text":"And the only thing we do"},{"time":496520,"text":"is send to the robot\nthrough a remote control"},{"time":498720,"text":"the two descending signals\nit normally should receive"},{"time":501240,"text":"from the upper part of the brain."},{"time":503480,"text":"And what's interesting is,\nby playing with these signals,"},{"time":506200,"text":"we can completely control\nspeed, heading and type of gait."},{"time":509600,"text":"For instance,"},{"time":510840,"text":"when we stimulate at a low level,\nwe have the walking gait,"},{"time":514440,"text":"and at some point, if we stimulate a lot,"},{"time":516440,"text":"very rapidly it switches\nto the swimming gait."},{"time":519480,"text":"And finally, we can also\ndo turning very nicely"},{"time":521720,"text":"by just stimulating more one side\nof the spinal cord than the other."},{"time":526200,"text":"And I think it's really beautiful"},{"time":527840,"text":"how nature has distributed control"},{"time":530120,"text":"to really give a lot of responsibility\nto the spinal cord"},{"time":533000,"text":"so that the upper part of the brain\ndoesn't need to worry about every muscle."},{"time":536680,"text":"It just has to worry\nabout this high-level modulation,"},{"time":539240,"text":"and it's really the job of the spinal cord\nto coordinate all the muscles."}]},{"cues":[{"time":542840,"text":"So now let's go to cat locomotion\nand the importance of biomechanics."},{"time":547080,"text":"So this is another project"},{"time":548360,"text":"where we studied cat biomechanics,"},{"time":550800,"text":"and we wanted to see how much\nthe morphology helps locomotion."},{"time":554720,"text":"And we found three important\ncriteria in the properties,"},{"time":558360,"text":"basically, of the limbs."},{"time":560320,"text":"The first one is that a cat limb"},{"time":562320,"text":"more or less looks\nlike a pantograph-like structure."},{"time":565040,"text":"So a pantograph is a mechanical structure"},{"time":567280,"text":"which keeps the upper segment\nand the lower segments always parallel."},{"time":571600,"text":"So a simple geometrical system\nthat kind of coordinates a bit"},{"time":574720,"text":"the internal movement of the segments."},{"time":576560,"text":"A second property of cat limbs\nis that they are very lightweight."},{"time":579640,"text":"Most of the muscles are in the trunk,"},{"time":581520,"text":"which is a good idea,\nbecause then the limbs have low inertia"},{"time":584440,"text":"and can be moved very rapidly."},{"time":586240,"text":"The last final important property is this\nvery elastic behavior of the cat limb,"},{"time":590080,"text":"so to handle impacts and forces."},{"time":592760,"text":"And this is how we designed Cheetah-Cub."}]},{"cues":[{"time":595120,"text":"So let's invite Cheetah-Cub onstage."},{"time":602160,"text":"So this is Peter Eckert,\nwho does his PhD on this robot,"},{"time":605840,"text":"and as you see, it's a cute little robot."},{"time":607920,"text":"It looks a bit like a toy,"},{"time":609200,"text":"but it was really used\nas a scientific tool"},{"time":611280,"text":"to investigate these properties\nof the legs of the cat."},{"time":614600,"text":"So you see, it's very compliant,\nvery lightweight,"},{"time":617240,"text":"and also very elastic,"},{"time":618520,"text":"so you can easily press it down\nand it will not break."},{"time":621320,"text":"It will just jump, in fact."},{"time":622800,"text":"And this very elastic property\nis also very important."},{"time":627160,"text":"And you also see a bit these properties"},{"time":629080,"text":"of these three segments\nof the leg as pantograph."}]},{"cues":[{"time":632280,"text":"Now, what's interesting\nis that this quite dynamic gait"},{"time":635080,"text":"is obtained purely in open loop,"},{"time":637000,"text":"meaning no sensors,\nno complex feedback loops."},{"time":640160,"text":"And that's interesting, because it means"},{"time":642600,"text":"that just the mechanics\nalready stabilized this quite rapid gait,"},{"time":646640,"text":"and that really good mechanics\nalready basically simplify locomotion."},{"time":650840,"text":"To the extent that we can even\ndisturb a bit locomotion,"},{"time":654160,"text":"as you will see in the next video,"},{"time":655840,"text":"where we can for instance do some exercise\nwhere we have the robot go down a step,"},{"time":659760,"text":"and the robot will not fall over,"},{"time":661400,"text":"which was a surprise for us."},{"time":663000,"text":"This is a small perturbation."},{"time":664440,"text":"I was expecting the robot\nto immediately fall over,"},{"time":666880,"text":"because there are no sensors,\nno fast feedback loop."},{"time":669340,"text":"But no, just the mechanics\nstabilized the gait,"},{"time":671560,"text":"and the robot doesn't fall over."},{"time":673160,"text":"Obviously, if you make the step bigger,\nand if you have obstacles,"},{"time":676320,"text":"you need the full control loops\nand reflexes and everything."},{"time":680000,"text":"But what's important here\nis that just for small perturbation,"},{"time":682960,"text":"the mechanics are right."},{"time":684480,"text":"And I think this is\na very important message"},{"time":686600,"text":"from biomechanics and robotics\nto neuroscience,"},{"time":688815,"text":"saying don't underestimate to what extent\nthe body already helps locomotion."}]},{"cues":[{"time":695440,"text":"Now, how does this relate\nto human locomotion?"},{"time":697960,"text":"Clearly, human locomotion is more complex\nthan cat and salamander locomotion,"},{"time":702360,"text":"but at the same time, the nervous system\nof humans is very similar"},{"time":705520,"text":"to that of other vertebrates."},{"time":707120,"text":"And especially the spinal cord"},{"time":708600,"text":"is also the key controller\nfor locomotion in humans."},{"time":711760,"text":"That's why, if there's a lesion\nof the spinal cord,"},{"time":714200,"text":"this has dramatic effects."},{"time":715720,"text":"The person can become\nparaplegic or tetraplegic."},{"time":718520,"text":"This is because the brain\nloses this communication"},{"time":720920,"text":"with the spinal cord."},{"time":722200,"text":"Especially, it loses\nthis descending modulation"},{"time":724440,"text":"to initiate and modulate locomotion."},{"time":727640,"text":"So a big goal of neuroprosthetics"},{"time":729360,"text":"is to be able to reactivate\nthat communication"},{"time":731760,"text":"using electrical or chemical stimulations."},{"time":734840,"text":"And there are several teams\nin the world that do exactly that,"},{"time":737800,"text":"especially at EPFL."},{"time":739040,"text":"My colleagues Grégoire Courtine\nand Silvestro Micera,"},{"time":741560,"text":"with whom I collaborate."}]},{"cues":[{"time":743960,"text":"But to do this properly,\nit's very important to understand"},{"time":747080,"text":"how the spinal cord works,"},{"time":748840,"text":"how it interacts with the body,"},{"time":750560,"text":"and how the brain\ncommunicates with the spinal cord."},{"time":753800,"text":"This is where the robots\nand models that I've presented today"},{"time":756720,"text":"will hopefully play a key role"},{"time":758640,"text":"towards these very important goals."}]},{"cues":[{"time":761320,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":762560,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":772100,"text":"Bruno Giussani: Auke, I've seen\nin your lab other robots"},{"time":774760,"text":"that do things like swim in pollution"},{"time":777240,"text":"and measure the pollution while they swim."},{"time":779720,"text":"But for this one,"},{"time":780960,"text":"you mentioned in your talk,\nlike a side project,"},{"time":785640,"text":"search and rescue,"},{"time":786880,"text":"and it does have a camera on its nose."}]},{"cues":[{"time":789080,"text":"Auke Ijspeert: Absolutely. So the robot --"},{"time":791600,"text":"We have some spin-off projects"},{"time":793053,"text":"where we would like to use the robots\nto do search and rescue inspection,"},{"time":796520,"text":"so this robot is now seeing you."},{"time":798120,"text":"And the big dream is to,\nif you have a difficult situation"},{"time":801320,"text":"like a collapsed building\nor a building that is flooded,"},{"time":804960,"text":"and this is very dangerous\nfor a rescue team or even rescue dogs,"},{"time":808320,"text":"why not send in a robot\nthat can crawl around, swim, walk,"},{"time":811240,"text":"with a camera onboard\nto do inspection and identify survivors"},{"time":814440,"text":"and possibly create\na communication link with the survivor."}]},{"cues":[{"time":817240,"text":"BG: Of course, assuming the survivors\ndon't get scared by the shape of this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":820840,"text":"AI: Yeah, we should probably\nchange the appearance quite a bit,"},{"time":824160,"text":"because here I guess a survivor\nmight die of a heart attack"},{"time":827000,"text":"just of being worried\nthat this would feed on you."},{"time":829560,"text":"But by changing the appearance\nand it making it more robust,"},{"time":832440,"text":"I'm sure we can make\na good tool out of it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":834520,"text":"BG: Thank you very much.\nThank you and your team."}]}]}